Requirements

Use-case

  • Provide <1.2ms network latency to a specific Provider
  • Peering in Amsterdam and Frankfurt area
  • Use a IaaS provider who provide virtual routers
  • Future new PoPs over other IaaS providers or On-premises

What is expected from us?

  • Router Configuration
    • High-availability, critical business operation $$$
    • No network engineers to operate it
    • DevOps teams, building and running it, easy to adapt
  • Network Monitoring
    • Integrate with current SaaS monitoring solutions

Templates

    # BGP peerings
{% for peer in config['peers'] %}
    {% if peer.multi_hop != 0 %}
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} ebgp-multihop {{ peer.multi_hop }}
    {% endif %}
    {% if peer.med %}
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} route-map export 'MED100'
    {% endif %}
    {% if peer.localpref %}
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} route-map import 'SETLOCALPREF'
    {% endif %}
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} prefix-list export 'EXPORT-IP-RANGES'
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} remote-as {{ peer.asn }}
    set protocols bgp {{ config['asn'] }} neighbor {{ peer.ip }} soft-reconfiguration 'inbound'
{% endfor %}

Lessons learned

  • Don't have fear, there are friends willing to help!
  • Learn failure after failure
  • Start small, solve concrete issues
  • When everything is running, destroy it and recreate from scratch
